1
00:00:31,984 --> 00:00:36,113
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

2
00:00:36,114 --> 00:00:40,493
10 YEARS AGO

3
00:00:41,244 --> 00:00:42,995
EPISODE 2

4
00:00:55,883 --> 00:00:57,468
Excuse me.

5
00:01:05,101 --> 00:01:06,185
Hello...

6
00:01:08,187 --> 00:01:09,522
Ms. Shibasaki?

7
00:01:22,869 --> 00:01:23,953
Shit!

8
00:01:24,203 --> 00:01:25,204
Black Pearl.

9
00:01:25,788 --> 00:01:27,665
You've developed a foul mouth
since we last met.

10
00:01:35,298 --> 00:01:36,549
Bulgae...

11
00:01:37,842 --> 00:01:40,470
You son of a bitch.

12
00:02:23,804 --> 00:02:25,223
RESCUE EQUIPMENT BOX

13
00:02:37,443 --> 00:02:38,861
Hands up and get up slowly.

14
00:02:47,370 --> 00:02:48,871
I'd only heard rumors about you.

15
00:02:49,956 --> 00:02:51,666
I never thought Bulgae would be a woman.

16
00:02:52,917 --> 00:02:54,335
Don't try anything funny

17
00:02:54,627 --> 00:02:55,753
and hand over the bag.

18
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:25,157
Check the bathroom.

19
00:03:31,706 --> 00:03:32,957
- Boss.
- What is it?

20
00:03:38,546 --> 00:03:39,672
Damn it.

21
00:03:40,923 --> 00:03:42,007
- Hey, Gong-bok.
- Yes, sir.

22
00:03:42,008 --> 00:03:43,258
Keep an eye on them

23
00:03:43,259 --> 00:03:44,427
- and toss every room.
- Yes, sir.

24
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,680
Well? Are you going to hand it over?

25
00:04:55,373 --> 00:04:56,499
What the hell are you?

26
00:04:56,832 --> 00:04:58,041
You're a man?

27
00:04:58,042 --> 00:05:00,252
So you're not completely blind after all.

28
00:05:00,378 --> 00:05:01,796
And you're supposed to be
North Korea's top agent?

29
00:05:02,338 --> 00:05:03,713
What the hell? That's just perverted!

30
00:05:03,714 --> 00:05:06,049
Ever heard of an operational disguise?

31
00:05:06,050 --> 00:05:07,802
I don't care if it's for an operation.

32
00:05:08,594 --> 00:05:10,638
Damn it. When you lifted your leg...

33
00:05:14,183 --> 00:05:16,060
How disgusting. I can't exactly fight
with my eyes closed.

34
00:05:16,602 --> 00:05:18,020
You could've at least shaved!

35
00:05:18,646 --> 00:05:20,106
Are you all talk?

36
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,484
Enough talk and come at me.

37
00:07:34,323 --> 00:07:36,367
You damn son of a bitch.

38
00:08:04,728 --> 00:08:05,812
What are you doing?

39
00:08:05,813 --> 00:08:07,314
Hurry and pull me up!

40
00:08:48,898 --> 00:08:53,402
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

41
00:09:00,868 --> 00:09:01,869
Damn it.

42
00:09:26,435 --> 00:09:29,313
Who the hell are you, you bastard?

43
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,566
You bastard.

44
00:09:32,691 --> 00:09:33,692
Uncle.

45
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,284
HEO NAM-IL, 64 HAGEUN-RO, YEONGSAN-GUN

46
00:09:46,163 --> 00:09:47,164
Let's go.

47
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,501
You bastard.

48
00:10:00,344 --> 00:10:01,387
What the hell...

49
00:10:32,251 --> 00:10:33,669
HEAVEN HOTEL

50
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:38,882
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

51
00:10:44,096 --> 00:10:46,015
The only thing on the USB you gave us

52
00:10:46,223 --> 00:10:48,058
was this CCTV footage, Prosecutor.

53
00:10:49,226 --> 00:10:52,438
A ferry from 2016.

54
00:10:56,191 --> 00:10:58,068
This article seems to be from
around that time.

55
00:10:59,611 --> 00:11:01,572
The footage and the gun...

56
00:11:02,281 --> 00:11:03,823
What kind of person

57
00:11:03,824 --> 00:11:06,201
builds a secret room
just to hide things like this?

58
00:11:06,326 --> 00:11:07,995
She was no ordinary civilian.

59
00:11:08,495 --> 00:11:10,122
The pistol from that room

60
00:11:10,372 --> 00:11:12,583
is a Russian model used
by North Korean soldiers.

61
00:11:13,584 --> 00:11:15,502
So, the dead woman
was a North Korean soldier...

62
00:11:15,878 --> 00:11:17,087
Is that what you mean?

63
00:11:20,424 --> 00:11:22,843
But why would a woman like her
commit suicide in our country?

64
00:11:24,428 --> 00:11:25,763
Rather than a suicide

65
00:11:26,096 --> 00:11:29,474
it's more likely she was murdered
after being exposed in a NewTube video.

66
00:11:29,475 --> 00:11:30,934
That's a more plausible theory.

67
00:11:31,351 --> 00:11:33,353
It seemed like she was living in hiding.

68
00:11:33,562 --> 00:11:35,064
Laying low

69
00:11:35,439 --> 00:11:37,149
and going through the data here.

70
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:39,317
Let's start

71
00:11:39,318 --> 00:11:41,945
by identifying the people
in the CCTV footage.

72
00:11:42,154 --> 00:11:43,989
We need to get the passenger list
from the ferry.

73
00:11:44,198 --> 00:11:45,199
Yes, ma'am.

74
00:11:49,828 --> 00:11:51,121
Yes, this is Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

75
00:11:51,789 --> 00:11:52,790
Yes, Chief Prosecutor.

76
00:11:54,708 --> 00:11:55,709
Right now?

77
00:11:57,044 --> 00:11:58,045
Prosecutor Gang.

78
00:11:58,378 --> 00:11:59,463
are you out of your mind?

79
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,298
You just got transferred

80
00:12:01,465 --> 00:12:03,174
and you're already reopening a closed case

81
00:12:03,175 --> 00:12:04,718
that you decided on your own

82
00:12:05,219 --> 00:12:06,303
to go to the scene?

83
00:12:07,137 --> 00:12:08,806
When you go around
stirring things up like that

84
00:12:08,931 --> 00:12:10,973
do you know
what they say about prosecutors?

85
00:12:10,974 --> 00:12:14,394
That they're just giving
hard-working cops the runaround!

86
00:12:16,355 --> 00:12:17,731
Have you not heard that?

87
00:12:20,526 --> 00:12:21,527
I have not.

88
00:12:23,862 --> 00:12:25,072
I was not aware of that.

89
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:29,243
What? You weren't aware?

90
00:12:30,494 --> 00:12:32,036
Oh, I am terribly sorry.

91
00:12:32,037 --> 00:12:33,956
I guess I, once again,
failed to read the room.

92
00:12:35,541 --> 00:12:37,417
I let my eagerness get the better of me.

93
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:40,087
I am so very sorry

94
00:12:40,504 --> 00:12:41,505
for causing you this trouble.

95
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,758
Whether it's a written reprimand
or a pay cut

96
00:12:45,634 --> 00:12:46,635
I'll accept it.

97
00:12:49,596 --> 00:12:50,639
This one time...

98
00:12:51,098 --> 00:12:53,267
I'll let it slide and take the blame.

99
00:12:54,017 --> 00:12:55,018
But this case...

100
00:12:55,602 --> 00:12:56,979
If I hear that Prosecutor Gang

101
00:12:57,646 --> 00:13:00,023
is poking around again

102
00:13:00,274 --> 00:13:02,943
I'll have you transferred to some
backwater branch office.

103
00:13:03,944 --> 00:13:04,945
Yes, sir.

104
00:13:12,828 --> 00:13:15,371
I made sure she won't go

105
00:13:15,372 --> 00:13:17,124
near the case again.

106
00:13:20,586 --> 00:13:22,212
The new troublemaker

107
00:13:22,462 --> 00:13:24,798
seems to have gotten a bit overzealous.

108
00:13:25,174 --> 00:13:26,466
Are you sure?

109
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:28,259
Yes.

110
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:31,180
Well, I've already gotten the police
on the same page.

111
00:13:31,638 --> 00:13:33,932
What could possibly happen now?

112
00:13:35,851 --> 00:13:39,479
I should be treating you
to a meal in person

113
00:13:39,855 --> 00:13:40,856
but it's election season.

114
00:13:41,398 --> 00:13:42,524
Instead, tonight

115
00:13:43,066 --> 00:13:45,360
I'll send my regards through Chief Baek.

116
00:13:45,861 --> 00:13:46,862
All right.

117
00:13:54,077 --> 00:13:55,370
Representative Kim Jung-hyeok is here.

118
00:13:55,704 --> 00:13:57,164
- Show him in.
- Yes, sir.

119
00:14:00,626 --> 00:14:02,211
Goodness.

120
00:14:02,419 --> 00:14:05,005
You've got a great view here, huh?

121
00:14:05,756 --> 00:14:08,008
You can see all of Imcheon from up here.

122
00:14:08,217 --> 00:14:10,052
It's quite a sight, isn't it?

123
00:14:10,886 --> 00:14:11,887
You're too kind.

124
00:14:14,014 --> 00:14:17,392
FLOOR LEADER OF THE SAEHANJIN PARTY,
KIM JUNG-HYEOK

125
00:14:18,310 --> 00:14:21,855
But you know, standing here like this...

126
00:14:22,856 --> 00:14:26,068
there's one thing I just don't understand.

127
00:14:28,153 --> 00:14:29,988
Why would the great Han Gyeong-wook

128
00:14:30,113 --> 00:14:32,574
give up this office with its amazing view

129
00:14:32,741 --> 00:14:34,200
and be so desperate

130
00:14:34,201 --> 00:14:36,536
to get into
that run-down city hall building?

131
00:14:36,954 --> 00:14:38,788
What's in it for you

132
00:14:38,789 --> 00:14:40,165
being the mayor of some backwater town?

133
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:42,459
Besides, in Imcheon

134
00:14:42,793 --> 00:14:44,877
Kim Seon-jung, who's also running

135
00:14:44,878 --> 00:14:46,712
has the place on lock.

136
00:14:46,713 --> 00:14:49,049
To go out of your way
to turn down an easy path

137
00:14:49,299 --> 00:14:50,842
and wade through filth

138
00:14:51,051 --> 00:14:53,512
just to run in this election...

139
00:14:54,304 --> 00:14:57,432
There must be a very good reason.

140
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:01,185
Why don't we sit
and discuss it over some tea?

141
00:15:01,186 --> 00:15:03,063
I just got some excellent tea in.

142
00:15:04,815 --> 00:15:06,066
Look.

143
00:15:06,483 --> 00:15:07,775
During election season

144
00:15:07,776 --> 00:15:09,527
do you think you're the only one

145
00:15:09,528 --> 00:15:10,988
inviting me for tea?

146
00:15:11,321 --> 00:15:12,905
After you give me an answer

147
00:15:12,906 --> 00:15:15,449
I'll decide whether or not
to have that tea.

148
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:16,493
Well...

149
00:15:17,411 --> 00:15:19,788
Your insight is truly unparalleled, sir.

150
00:15:22,457 --> 00:15:23,667
Sir, have you ever...

151
00:15:24,084 --> 00:15:25,794
heard of Yeongseon Island?

152
00:15:25,961 --> 00:15:27,170
Yeongseon Island?

153
00:15:27,671 --> 00:15:29,715
You mean, because of one island

154
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,090
you started this whole thing?

155
00:15:31,091 --> 00:15:33,385
Let me explain it in a way
that's easy to understand.

156
00:15:33,719 --> 00:15:34,720
Please, have a seat.

157
00:15:35,012 --> 00:15:36,013
Yeongseon Island

158
00:15:36,596 --> 00:15:38,223
is a bit far from the mainland

159
00:15:38,473 --> 00:15:41,351
but with major Northeast Asian countries
like China and Japan

160
00:15:41,476 --> 00:15:42,685
it's a geographical strongpoint

161
00:15:42,686 --> 00:15:44,938
perfectly optimized for maritime trade.

162
00:15:45,355 --> 00:15:46,773
Its tourism resources aren't bad either.

163
00:15:47,024 --> 00:15:48,275
The only downside is

164
00:15:48,692 --> 00:15:50,693
it's tied up in too many regulations

165
00:15:50,694 --> 00:15:53,030
for environmental and domestic protection.

166
00:15:53,363 --> 00:15:54,697
Because of that, right now,

167
00:15:54,698 --> 00:15:57,366
there's only one casino
for locals barely operating.

168
00:15:57,367 --> 00:16:00,662
But if we let wealthy foreigners run
businesses there without regulations...

169
00:16:00,829 --> 00:16:02,371
If we loosen what needs to be loosened

170
00:16:02,372 --> 00:16:03,790
and turn a blind eye to what we must

171
00:16:03,957 --> 00:16:05,042
what do you think will happen?

172
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:07,626
Yeongseon Island could easily

173
00:16:07,627 --> 00:16:09,880
become the biggest pleasure
island in Asia.

174
00:16:10,797 --> 00:16:11,882
You don't mean...

175
00:16:12,299 --> 00:16:14,717
- Already?
- For tourism developers in Northeast Asia

176
00:16:14,718 --> 00:16:15,843
Yeongseon Island

177
00:16:15,844 --> 00:16:18,555
is the perfect location
to use as a business hub.

178
00:16:18,847 --> 00:16:21,683
Many companies have already
expressed their interest in participating.

179
00:16:22,267 --> 00:16:23,810
If we sell off pieces of the island

180
00:16:24,311 --> 00:16:27,522
we could generate
a profit of about 25 trillion won.

181
00:16:27,773 --> 00:16:30,359
25... 25 trillion?

182
00:16:30,525 --> 00:16:31,650
With that kind of money

183
00:16:31,651 --> 00:16:34,738
for you to become president in four years

184
00:16:35,781 --> 00:16:37,491
wouldn't that be a good stepping stone?

185
00:16:37,741 --> 00:16:40,327
Do you really think this will pan out
the way you've imagined?

186
00:16:40,994 --> 00:16:43,789
I mean, Kim Seon-jung
will be tough to deal with.

187
00:16:43,914 --> 00:16:45,749
If you would just give it a little push

188
00:16:46,249 --> 00:16:47,834
wouldn't things go much more smoothly?

189
00:16:53,924 --> 00:16:55,884
Oh, right. Is that tea ready?

190
00:16:56,259 --> 00:16:57,469
I heard you got something special.

191
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:08,896
This was sold to China by Kim Jong-il
during the Arduous March.

192
00:17:09,481 --> 00:17:10,773
It's a bronze ewer.

193
00:17:12,192 --> 00:17:14,903
I acquired it through a connection
from my time at the NIS.

194
00:17:15,737 --> 00:17:17,154
If you'll allow me

195
00:17:17,155 --> 00:17:19,116
I'd like to present it to you as a gift.

196
00:17:20,157 --> 00:17:21,492
Will you accept it?

197
00:18:03,702 --> 00:18:06,037
This is the woman
Kim Jung-hyeok has been seeing lately.

198
00:18:06,413 --> 00:18:08,748
He gifted her a three-story café building
in Gangnam behind his family's back

199
00:18:08,957 --> 00:18:10,959
and it looks like there was
some tax evasion involved.

200
00:18:14,963 --> 00:18:17,298
We need that to keep a leash
on the old geezer

201
00:18:17,299 --> 00:18:18,717
- so keep it safe.
- Yes, sir.

202
00:18:19,009 --> 00:18:20,093
By the way.

203
00:18:20,343 --> 00:18:22,887
How's the land acquisition
on Yeongseon Island coming along?

204
00:18:22,888 --> 00:18:24,472
Due to strong opposition
from the residents

205
00:18:24,473 --> 00:18:25,848
it's been slightly delayed.

206
00:18:25,849 --> 00:18:27,433
Yoo In-gu went down to handle it himself

207
00:18:27,434 --> 00:18:28,977
- so if you'll just wait...
- Joong-ki.

208
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:31,271
You're taking too long.

209
00:18:32,147 --> 00:18:33,148
Get it?

210
00:18:35,025 --> 00:18:36,067
My apologies.

211
00:18:36,359 --> 00:18:37,903
I'll instruct them to push
this forward as much as possible.

212
00:18:46,786 --> 00:18:50,040
Hey, I told you to just put your
thumbprint on it so we can finish up.

213
00:18:50,582 --> 00:18:52,375
I said that's our ancestral land

214
00:18:52,626 --> 00:18:54,544
so it's not for sale.

215
00:18:54,669 --> 00:18:57,004
This old fool still doesn't get it.

216
00:18:57,005 --> 00:18:59,507
Look, the money I borrowed...

217
00:18:59,508 --> 00:19:01,759
I'll take care of it this week.

218
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,344
- Please...
- Hey, he hasn't had enough.

219
00:19:03,345 --> 00:19:04,346
Get him.

220
00:19:06,515 --> 00:19:08,265
Kkot-nim. Business going well?

221
00:19:08,266 --> 00:19:09,309
Hello, boss!

222
00:19:10,143 --> 00:19:11,644
You should've called before you came.

223
00:19:11,645 --> 00:19:12,728
What brings you here?

224
00:19:12,729 --> 00:19:14,773
I've gotta make it look like I'm doing
something, right?

225
00:19:14,898 --> 00:19:17,150
Chief Han is raising hell,
telling us to get a move on.

226
00:19:18,026 --> 00:19:19,735
Boss, you know we're on it.

227
00:19:19,736 --> 00:19:22,155
- Sector A will be wrapped up soon.
- So I see.

228
00:19:22,697 --> 00:19:24,991
- Are you doing what I told you?
- Of course, boss.

229
00:19:47,639 --> 00:19:50,559
Jeez, the jerky business is booming, huh?

230
00:19:52,143 --> 00:19:55,230
But boss, are you sure it's okay to be
running a business behind his back?

231
00:19:55,689 --> 00:19:57,440
Chief Han is not someone
to be trifled with.

232
00:19:58,233 --> 00:19:59,858
Hey, that guy's too busy

233
00:19:59,859 --> 00:20:02,070
driving around in that truck
giving speeches.

234
00:20:03,071 --> 00:20:05,657
We're going to get a big cut once the
Yeongseon Island deal is done anyway,

235
00:20:06,241 --> 00:20:08,159
so I'm worried this is just stirring up
unnecessary trouble.

236
00:20:08,785 --> 00:20:10,912
You loyal bastard.

237
00:20:11,371 --> 00:20:13,080
Just wait until this Yeongseon Island deal
is done.

238
00:20:13,081 --> 00:20:15,332
You think that viper Chief Han
and that vixen Chairman Do

239
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,836
are going to reward their underlings
for a job well done?

240
00:20:18,253 --> 00:20:20,922
We'll be lucky if they don't
trump up a charge and screw us over.

241
00:20:21,339 --> 00:20:22,715
Before that

242
00:20:22,716 --> 00:20:25,594
we need to grab everything we can.

243
00:20:25,802 --> 00:20:27,512
If we don't want to end up empty-handed.

244
00:20:29,222 --> 00:20:30,432
So that was your grand plan.

245
00:20:30,765 --> 00:20:31,766
Boss!

246
00:20:32,642 --> 00:20:34,019
There's a problem at the capital firm.

247
00:20:57,751 --> 00:20:58,752
What's this?

248
00:21:00,045 --> 00:21:01,046
My arm...

249
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:05,800
Why won't my arm move?

250
00:21:08,345 --> 00:21:09,387
Uncle, Uncle!

251
00:21:10,221 --> 00:21:11,222
Are you okay?

252
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:15,268
Shouldn't you still be in bed?

253
00:21:15,602 --> 00:21:17,854
When...

254
00:21:18,730 --> 00:21:20,565
did I get home?

255
00:21:21,816 --> 00:21:23,525
I remember going for the house deed

256
00:21:23,526 --> 00:21:25,362
and getting beaten up

257
00:21:25,945 --> 00:21:27,113
but that's it.

258
00:21:27,447 --> 00:21:29,491
Uncle, don't worry about the deed.

259
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,409
I got them all back.

260
00:21:33,870 --> 00:21:34,871
Those bastards.

261
00:21:35,288 --> 00:21:38,625
Looks like they're determined to bleed the
people of Yeongseon Island dry.

262
00:21:40,543 --> 00:21:42,294
CERTIFIED COPY OF REAL ESTATE REGISTRY
BUILDING

263
00:21:42,295 --> 00:21:43,672
How did you get these back?

264
00:21:45,298 --> 00:21:46,299
What?

265
00:21:47,634 --> 00:21:48,677
You don't remember?

266
00:21:49,594 --> 00:21:50,595
No.

267
00:21:53,598 --> 00:21:56,017
I remember getting hit really hard once.

268
00:21:57,268 --> 00:21:58,853
After that one big hit...

269
00:22:02,232 --> 00:22:03,274
What happened?

270
00:22:07,404 --> 00:22:09,989
My whole body is aching.
Did I get beat up badly?

271
00:22:11,241 --> 00:22:12,367
Uncle.

272
00:22:12,701 --> 00:22:14,828
Getting beat up
isn't what matters right now.

273
00:22:16,371 --> 00:22:17,455
But, why are you...

274
00:22:18,998 --> 00:22:20,333
calling me "Uncle"?

275
00:22:21,459 --> 00:22:23,044
Not "Hey, you" like before.

276
00:22:24,713 --> 00:22:28,383
Oh, that's because I didn't really know
you back then.

277
00:22:29,968 --> 00:22:33,138
I'm telling you, it was like
watching a martial arts movie.

278
00:22:33,388 --> 00:22:35,598
- You're saying that's me?
- Yeah!

279
00:22:36,224 --> 00:22:38,100
All of a sudden, you just snapped.

280
00:22:38,101 --> 00:22:39,102
You were, like...

281
00:22:40,937 --> 00:22:42,187
And after a few moves

282
00:22:42,188 --> 00:22:43,606
you just wiped the floor with them.

283
00:22:45,608 --> 00:22:46,776
I don't remember any of that.

284
00:22:49,028 --> 00:22:51,489
Are you sure you're not lying to cover up
something you did?

285
00:22:51,823 --> 00:22:52,990
Come on

286
00:22:52,991 --> 00:22:55,118
why would I make something like that up?

287
00:22:55,618 --> 00:22:56,745
Watch again. See?

288
00:23:02,083 --> 00:23:03,167
How can that be me?

289
00:23:03,168 --> 00:23:04,918
I think when things got dangerous

290
00:23:04,919 --> 00:23:06,963
your hidden past must have come out.

291
00:23:08,214 --> 00:23:10,257
- A hidden past?
- Yeah.

292
00:23:10,258 --> 00:23:12,135
You know, like in the movies.

293
00:23:12,343 --> 00:23:13,886
When the hero is in danger

294
00:23:13,887 --> 00:23:16,806
their past just suddenly
comes flashing back.

295
00:23:17,390 --> 00:23:19,517
Anything coming back to you, Uncle?

296
00:23:21,060 --> 00:23:22,353
No, my head just hurts.

297
00:23:23,897 --> 00:23:27,025
So I came up with a theory.

298
00:23:27,484 --> 00:23:29,277
Who are you really, Uncle?

299
00:23:29,736 --> 00:23:30,945
How can you be such a good fighter?

300
00:23:32,906 --> 00:23:34,199
And the answer became obvious.

301
00:23:35,784 --> 00:23:36,868
A 007 agent.

302
00:23:37,744 --> 00:23:39,161
And I never said it

303
00:23:39,162 --> 00:23:40,747
but I always thought the vibe you give off

304
00:23:40,955 --> 00:23:42,749
was really intense.

305
00:23:45,293 --> 00:23:47,045
I suppose I do have that side to me.

306
00:23:50,381 --> 00:23:52,133
Is it that obvious to you?

307
00:23:53,009 --> 00:23:54,177
Yeah, I'm telling you!

308
00:23:56,387 --> 00:23:57,596
Bulgae showed up!

309
00:23:57,597 --> 00:24:00,225
- It was Bulgae!
- Hey, Ho-myeong, calm down.

310
00:24:00,642 --> 00:24:02,559
Seong-won, run a trace
on a motorcycle plate.

311
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:04,813
It's Imcheon, Yeongseon-ga

312
00:24:05,021 --> 00:24:06,522
- 9342.
- Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong!

313
00:24:06,523 --> 00:24:08,732
No, on second thought, you get down here.
We'll look for him together.

314
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:10,734
The more you rush,
the more careful you have to be.

315
00:24:10,735 --> 00:24:12,153
Have you already forgotten
what happened that day, ten years ago?

316
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,323
Ho-myeong

317
00:24:16,324 --> 00:24:18,618
I'll get you the plate search
results by tomorrow morning.

318
00:24:18,910 --> 00:24:20,369
You need to confirm
whether that guy is really Bulgae

319
00:24:20,370 --> 00:24:21,995
and if he actually has the goods.

320
00:24:21,996 --> 00:24:23,748
Focus on that first. All right?

321
00:24:23,957 --> 00:24:25,959
I'll finish up here and be right there.

322
00:24:26,501 --> 00:24:28,044
Okay? Be smart about this.

323
00:24:28,711 --> 00:24:30,046
- All right.
- Okay.

324
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:35,176
- That Jeong Ho-myeong...
- Hey, mister!

325
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:37,345
So, when's it going to be ready?

326
00:24:37,887 --> 00:24:39,305
Oh, yes. It'll be right out.

327
00:24:40,306 --> 00:24:42,100
- Good grief.
- I'm sorry.

328
00:24:42,642 --> 00:24:45,979
How long do I have to wait
for just one of these things? Seriously.

329
00:24:50,567 --> 00:24:51,984
Get out.

330
00:24:51,985 --> 00:24:54,111
I'm sorry, boss. I messed up, boss.

331
00:24:54,112 --> 00:24:55,989
- I just...
- Get out.

332
00:25:00,285 --> 00:25:01,618
Wait a minute. For real.

333
00:25:01,619 --> 00:25:03,204
Hold still, you bastard,
before you get hurt.

334
00:25:03,329 --> 00:25:04,955
It really hurts. It hurts so much.

335
00:25:04,956 --> 00:25:07,792
And the spot where that guy
hit me earlier still hurts like hell.

336
00:25:08,710 --> 00:25:10,919
You lose all the deeds
we worked so hard to collect

337
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,213
and now you're complaining
that you're in pain?

338
00:25:12,630 --> 00:25:14,966
I'm telling you, he was no ordinary guy.

339
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:18,594
The way his body was just flying around...

340
00:25:18,595 --> 00:25:20,470
He was like a martial arts master.

341
00:25:20,471 --> 00:25:22,139
And the other guy, the one in the hat...

342
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:24,100
his hands and feet were unbelievably fast.

343
00:25:24,350 --> 00:25:26,643
It made me wonder what guys like them were
doing in a backwater place like this.

344
00:25:26,644 --> 00:25:28,313
For real.

345
00:25:29,105 --> 00:25:30,982
What are you doing,
writing a restaurant review?

346
00:25:31,941 --> 00:25:34,027
- So how many stars?
- A lot... Wait, I'm sorry.

347
00:25:34,569 --> 00:25:36,361
Hey, you goddamn morons!

348
00:25:36,362 --> 00:25:37,988
If you're going to come back after getting
your asses handed to you

349
00:25:37,989 --> 00:25:41,074
you should've at least brought back a
video or a photo of the bastard's face!

350
00:25:41,075 --> 00:25:42,744
Come on, you know how it is, Boss.

351
00:25:43,161 --> 00:25:45,120
Our security cameras are just for show.

352
00:25:45,121 --> 00:25:47,040
In case any issues came up later

353
00:25:47,373 --> 00:25:49,791
you're the one who told us not to install
real cameras at the loan office.

354
00:25:49,792 --> 00:25:51,461
Don't you remember ordering that yourself?

355
00:25:52,045 --> 00:25:53,254
Right. So now it's my fault?

356
00:25:54,547 --> 00:25:55,548
- Hold it out.
- Yes, sir.

357
00:25:58,134 --> 00:25:59,968
Wait, that really hurts!

358
00:25:59,969 --> 00:26:00,970
I'm so sorry...

359
00:26:04,015 --> 00:26:05,182
All of you, get up!

360
00:26:05,183 --> 00:26:07,185
Oh, what do I do?

361
00:26:11,606 --> 00:26:12,690
- Hey.
- Yes, sir.

362
00:26:13,232 --> 00:26:15,150
Go sweet-talk the hotel security team

363
00:26:15,151 --> 00:26:16,444
and get the lobby's CCTV footage.

364
00:26:17,153 --> 00:26:18,613
Do it quietly, without Chairman Do
finding out.

365
00:26:18,863 --> 00:26:20,782
Why without Chairman Do finding out?

366
00:26:20,907 --> 00:26:22,742
Hey, you idiot. Can't you think?

367
00:26:22,909 --> 00:26:24,910
Chairman Do is just dying to
get rid of us.

368
00:26:24,911 --> 00:26:26,412
If she finds out this happened

369
00:26:27,121 --> 00:26:28,539
do you think she'd just let us be?

370
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:31,416
And if word gets out about trouble at one
of our spots, and Chief Han hears about it

371
00:26:31,417 --> 00:26:33,252
- don't you know we're finished?
- Right.

372
00:26:35,046 --> 00:26:36,296
You have three days

373
00:26:36,297 --> 00:26:38,132
to catch those bastards
and drag them here to me.

374
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,217
I don't care if he's a martial arts
master or just some guy in a cap.

375
00:26:40,218 --> 00:26:41,386
I'll kill him myself.

376
00:26:41,636 --> 00:26:42,637
Yes, I understand, Boss.

377
00:26:43,388 --> 00:26:44,930
Answer, you bastards! Damn it.

378
00:26:44,931 --> 00:26:45,974
- Yes, Boss!
- Yes, Boss!

379
00:26:46,766 --> 00:26:47,850
But, Boss...

380
00:26:48,810 --> 00:26:49,811
Where do I find them?

381
00:26:52,647 --> 00:26:54,732
- You want me to put it in your GPS?
- I'm sorry.

382
00:26:55,108 --> 00:26:57,026
What are you waiting for? Go! Now!

383
00:26:57,318 --> 00:26:59,277
Let's go! Come on, let's move!

384
00:26:59,278 --> 00:27:00,279
Damn it!

385
00:27:01,155 --> 00:27:02,239
I'm serious.

386
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:04,450
The loan sharks were all beaten to a pulp.

387
00:27:05,952 --> 00:27:07,035
So?

388
00:27:07,036 --> 00:27:08,079
What do you mean, so?

389
00:27:08,538 --> 00:27:11,206
This is a guy who hasn't gotten a single
speeding ticket in ten years.

390
00:27:11,207 --> 00:27:12,917
He must've had a reason for making a move.

391
00:27:13,793 --> 00:27:15,335
Let's put him under 24-hour surveillance

392
00:27:15,336 --> 00:27:16,337
and get to the bottom of this.

393
00:27:16,462 --> 00:27:18,798
If you're on 24-hour surveillance,
what about our 24-hour convenience store?

394
00:27:19,966 --> 00:27:21,216
Well, we'll have to close up shop.

395
00:27:21,217 --> 00:27:23,511
That's fine by me.
I was getting sick of this place anyway.

396
00:27:23,845 --> 00:27:25,054
Jeez, Gong-bok.

397
00:27:25,346 --> 00:27:27,556
Were you late for your shift

398
00:27:27,557 --> 00:27:28,682
because you were doing this useless stuff?

399
00:27:28,683 --> 00:27:30,350
Who cares about my shift right now?

400
00:27:30,351 --> 00:27:31,685
He's made his move.

401
00:27:31,686 --> 00:27:33,771
The guy we've been watching for ten years.

402
00:27:33,896 --> 00:27:37,065
Our Boss, who was framed and sent to
prison, all our scattered guys...

403
00:27:37,066 --> 00:27:39,776
This could be our one chance to get it all
back. Why are you hesitating?

404
00:27:39,777 --> 00:27:41,695
I'm asking why he would suddenly make a
move now!

405
00:27:41,696 --> 00:27:42,779
There's no reason for it!

406
00:27:42,780 --> 00:27:44,407
That's what I'm saying we should find out.

407
00:27:44,949 --> 00:27:46,909
Come on. You never used to hesitate.
What's wrong?

408
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:52,415
Oh, I know. It's because of that cop,
isn't it? That lady cop.

409
00:27:54,333 --> 00:27:55,334
What?

410
00:27:57,378 --> 00:27:58,379
Well...

411
00:28:03,092 --> 00:28:05,470
Wow. Unbelievable.

412
00:28:05,928 --> 00:28:06,929
Hey.

413
00:28:07,305 --> 00:28:09,891
In what convenience store does the
part-timer spy on the owner, huh?

414
00:28:11,851 --> 00:28:12,935
What did you just say?

415
00:28:13,061 --> 00:28:14,145
- Part-timer?
- Yep.

416
00:28:15,313 --> 00:28:17,440
- Am I just a part-timer at this store?
- Yeah.

417
00:28:19,358 --> 00:28:20,818
Okay, I see how you really feel.

418
00:28:21,027 --> 00:28:22,110
As for Jeong Ho-myeong

419
00:28:22,111 --> 00:28:24,906
I'll keep a close watch on him by myself.

420
00:28:28,701 --> 00:28:30,786
Go, just go! Fine, go.

421
00:28:30,787 --> 00:28:31,913
Hey, pay for that!

422
00:28:32,371 --> 00:28:34,165
Wait, don't go!
You have to take over for me!

423
00:28:35,083 --> 00:28:37,085
I just pulled an all-nighter!

424
00:29:36,936 --> 00:29:38,104
Nice shot.

425
00:29:45,361 --> 00:29:46,404
CONVERTING TO MULTIMEDIA MESSAGE...

426
00:29:50,074 --> 00:29:53,202
Yes, Chief Kim. I just sent you a license
plate number. That's right.

427
00:29:53,911 --> 00:29:55,538
I have a favor to ask.

428
00:29:56,038 --> 00:29:58,833
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

429
00:30:07,091 --> 00:30:08,342
Why isn't he here yet?

430
00:30:11,095 --> 00:30:13,305
Still no word from Ho-myeong?

431
00:30:13,306 --> 00:30:15,683
Ho-myeong isn't capable
of collecting that debt.

432
00:30:16,058 --> 00:30:18,186
He'll be lucky if he doesn't get beaten up
by those thugs.

433
00:30:25,234 --> 00:30:27,110
Hey, looks like they didn't beat you up
too badly.

434
00:30:27,111 --> 00:30:28,905
- Why weren't you answering your phone?
- What about the tab?

435
00:30:29,322 --> 00:30:30,323
Did you get it?

436
00:30:31,282 --> 00:30:32,575
I'm a little tired.

437
00:30:33,075 --> 00:30:34,452
I'm going to go upstairs and rest.

438
00:30:35,119 --> 00:30:36,120
Hey, wait.

439
00:30:43,085 --> 00:30:44,336
See? I told you.

440
00:30:44,337 --> 00:30:45,922
I told you it was
too much for him, didn't I?

441
00:30:51,344 --> 00:30:54,472
Jeez, if a man is going to
go out there with some grit

442
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,807
he should at least come back with a few
bucks.

443
00:30:58,142 --> 00:31:00,811
Dad, you really don't know your
son-in-law at all, do you?

444
00:31:01,270 --> 00:31:04,148
From now on, absolutely no orders from
Heaven Capital.

445
00:31:04,315 --> 00:31:05,816
- Got it?
- Yeah, okay.

446
00:31:06,359 --> 00:31:07,442
Mister!

447
00:31:07,443 --> 00:31:08,569
- You got that?
- I got it.

448
00:31:20,456 --> 00:31:21,916
The more you rush,
the more careful you have to be.

449
00:31:22,917 --> 00:31:24,377
Have you already forgotten
what happened that day, ten years ago?

450
00:31:27,296 --> 00:31:29,214
You go to Yeongseon Island
and find Bulgae, okay?

451
00:31:29,215 --> 00:31:31,508
- Just find him.
- It's dangerous for you to go alone.

452
00:31:31,509 --> 00:31:32,802
- Let me go...
- No, don't come.

453
00:31:33,302 --> 00:31:35,887
Don't come and just lay low
until I contact you, all right?

454
00:31:35,888 --> 00:31:36,889
I'll be in touch.

455
00:31:59,704 --> 00:32:00,913
Han Gyeong-wook.

456
00:32:01,872 --> 00:32:03,624
Are you calling your superior by his name?

457
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:06,002
Did you forget the chain of command?

458
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:09,088
Han Gyeong-wook, you son of a bitch.

459
00:32:19,890 --> 00:32:22,601
So much for Team Leader Jo,
the champion of justice.

460
00:32:23,060 --> 00:32:25,604
Shaking in your boots
over a few measly bullets.

461
00:32:28,274 --> 00:32:29,734
I'll give you a chance to live.

462
00:32:30,318 --> 00:32:31,402
The location of the item...

463
00:32:31,861 --> 00:32:33,362
you guys know it, don't you?

464
00:32:33,863 --> 00:32:35,239
Did Jeong Ho-myeong come looking for it?

465
00:32:36,115 --> 00:32:37,158
Why?

466
00:32:40,119 --> 00:32:41,495
Even the great Han Gyeong-wook...

467
00:32:42,079 --> 00:32:43,080
is getting scared, I see.

468
00:32:46,042 --> 00:32:47,375
All right, fine.

469
00:32:47,376 --> 00:32:49,961
Well, if I get Jeong Ho-myeong here
and ask him myself

470
00:32:49,962 --> 00:32:51,296
I'm sure I'll get an answer.

471
00:32:51,297 --> 00:32:53,799
Yeah, good luck with that.

472
00:32:54,675 --> 00:32:57,594
You trained him,
so you know him best, right?

473
00:32:57,595 --> 00:32:59,387
Of course, I do.

474
00:32:59,388 --> 00:33:01,140
I know exactly what kind
of man Jeong Ho-myeong is.

475
00:33:02,516 --> 00:33:03,725
In terms of pure skill

476
00:33:03,726 --> 00:33:06,437
he's the best there is.

477
00:33:08,564 --> 00:33:10,733
But his weakness is
that he cares too much.

478
00:33:15,237 --> 00:33:18,782
Jeong Ho-myeong is fiercely l
oyal to his senior.

479
00:33:18,783 --> 00:33:20,743
If he hears that
Team Leader Jo Seong-won is dead

480
00:33:21,702 --> 00:33:22,912
he will show up

481
00:33:23,162 --> 00:33:25,122
at the funeral no matter what.

482
00:33:25,581 --> 00:33:26,582
Am I wrong?

483
00:33:36,092 --> 00:33:37,301
Looks like the counter-intelligence agents
have arrived.

484
00:33:38,094 --> 00:33:39,095
We should pull out now.

485
00:33:43,933 --> 00:33:45,100
Let's fall back for now.

486
00:33:45,101 --> 00:33:47,103
Post our agents
at all the places he might go.

487
00:33:47,478 --> 00:33:48,479
Understood.

488
00:33:54,443 --> 00:33:55,945
I won't lose him this time.

489
00:33:56,987 --> 00:33:57,988
Never.

490
00:33:58,697 --> 00:34:01,242
NIS AGENT MISSING... INTERNAL MANAGEMENT
FLAWS EXPOSED AT INTELLIGENCE AGENCY

491
00:34:14,045 --> 00:34:15,422
103BEO 8589

492
00:34:22,596 --> 00:34:25,764
- Yes, Chief Kim.
- I tailed the car like you asked.

493
00:34:25,766 --> 00:34:27,268
But do you really...

494
00:34:28,101 --> 00:34:29,226
need to know this?

495
00:34:29,228 --> 00:34:30,937
You couldn't track the owner's movements?

496
00:34:30,938 --> 00:34:32,147
No, that's not it.

497
00:34:32,148 --> 00:34:33,232
The owner of the car is...

498
00:34:35,943 --> 00:34:37,277
Han Gyeong-wook's secretary.

499
00:34:39,196 --> 00:34:40,239
Han Gyeong-wook?

500
00:34:41,364 --> 00:34:42,408
Yes.

501
00:34:43,534 --> 00:34:45,870
Han Gyeong-wook, the one running
for Mayor of Imcheon.

502
00:34:49,623 --> 00:34:50,748
Prosecutor.

503
00:34:50,748 --> 00:34:52,042
You should just drop this case.

504
00:34:52,918 --> 00:34:55,463
You were only just transferred here

505
00:34:55,795 --> 00:34:58,883
and I'm worried you'll be
shipped out again just as fast.

506
00:34:59,467 --> 00:35:00,468
And besides, right now...

507
00:35:04,597 --> 00:35:05,931
HAN GYEONG-WOOK

508
00:35:12,813 --> 00:35:15,024
A SPECIAL TOURISM ZONE WILL
REVITALIZE YEONGSEON ISLAND

509
00:35:20,196 --> 00:35:21,738
Han Gyeong-wook!

510
00:35:21,739 --> 00:35:30,372
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

511
00:35:30,873 --> 00:35:32,333
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

512
00:35:32,750 --> 00:35:34,084
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

513
00:35:50,601 --> 00:35:52,728
I've identified the owner of the
motorcycle you mentioned yesterday.

514
00:35:52,978 --> 00:35:53,979
But the owner...

515
00:35:54,230 --> 00:35:57,274
is a high school student with no
connection to Bulgae or North Korea.

516
00:36:05,241 --> 00:36:06,992
I'm done. I'll get it.

517
00:36:10,496 --> 00:36:12,206
Where are you going?
You were in the middle of peeling onions.

518
00:36:16,168 --> 00:36:17,502
I'm going to go drum up some business.

519
00:36:17,503 --> 00:36:19,212
- We need to increase sales.
- All of a sudden?

520
00:36:19,213 --> 00:36:20,714
Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong!

521
00:36:21,090 --> 00:36:22,091
Hey!

522
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:30,724
You little...

523
00:36:34,395 --> 00:36:35,812
We're just here to check something

524
00:36:35,813 --> 00:36:37,648
so let's not make this difficult for each
other.

525
00:36:37,982 --> 00:36:39,357
Make sure Chairman Do
doesn't hear about this.

526
00:36:39,358 --> 00:36:41,110
- You know what I mean?
- Yes.

527
00:36:42,069 --> 00:36:44,154
Kang-sik, give this kid
some money for medicine.

528
00:36:45,364 --> 00:36:47,533
Hurry up and find him. This isn't a game.

529
00:36:48,075 --> 00:36:49,868
- Boss!
- All right, Kang-sik found him.

530
00:36:50,244 --> 00:36:51,328
No, that's not it.

531
00:36:52,162 --> 00:36:53,163
Look at the lobby here.

532
00:36:54,540 --> 00:36:55,541
This guy.

533
00:36:55,874 --> 00:36:56,875
Isn't that Ma Gong-bok?

534
00:36:57,501 --> 00:36:58,502
Ma Gong-bok?

535
00:37:00,879 --> 00:37:02,756
Gong-bok showed up after ten years?

536
00:37:03,299 --> 00:37:04,592
On an island like this, of all places?

537
00:37:06,051 --> 00:37:07,303
Hey, Boss! We found him.

538
00:37:07,803 --> 00:37:08,804
It's that guy! That guy right there!

539
00:37:17,146 --> 00:37:18,439
Is this really him?

540
00:37:19,398 --> 00:37:21,275
He's so scrawny.
He looks like he couldn't hurt a fly.

541
00:37:21,984 --> 00:37:23,485
Oh, that's him all right, Boss.

542
00:37:27,364 --> 00:37:28,365
Hey, hey, hey!

543
00:37:30,659 --> 00:37:32,327
The guy who beat up my son

544
00:37:32,328 --> 00:37:34,330
and Gong-bok showed up on the same day?

545
00:37:42,296 --> 00:37:45,924
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

546
00:37:47,885 --> 00:37:49,219
- Aren't you going on patrol?
- What?

547
00:37:50,220 --> 00:37:51,263
MY CASH COW

548
00:37:52,181 --> 00:37:53,974
You guys go on ahead.

549
00:38:03,651 --> 00:38:05,610
Yes, hello?

550
00:38:05,611 --> 00:38:07,279
Hey, Officer Kim, how have you been?

551
00:38:07,529 --> 00:38:09,365
I'm doing well, thanks to you.

552
00:38:09,698 --> 00:38:11,282
So, what can I do for you?

553
00:38:11,283 --> 00:38:14,243
A small problem came up
at one of my businesses

554
00:38:14,244 --> 00:38:15,746
and I need you to look into something.

555
00:38:16,038 --> 00:38:17,622
I'm going to send you a few pictures.

556
00:38:17,623 --> 00:38:19,332
I need you to track down these two guys.

557
00:38:19,333 --> 00:38:21,125
If you look through the footage
from the road

558
00:38:21,126 --> 00:38:23,086
near the Heaven Hotel
around 3 o'clock yesterday

559
00:38:23,087 --> 00:38:24,420
it shouldn't be hard
to trace their movements.

560
00:38:24,421 --> 00:38:26,840
Okay. Please send the pictures.

561
00:38:35,641 --> 00:38:36,892
MY CASH COW

562
00:38:40,646 --> 00:38:42,981
YEONGSEON STEEL

563
00:39:02,835 --> 00:39:03,919
Manager Bong.

564
00:39:04,294 --> 00:39:06,004
Why did you skip work
yesterday without notice?

565
00:39:06,755 --> 00:39:07,756
Manager Lee.

566
00:39:07,965 --> 00:39:09,299
I'm so sorry.

567
00:39:10,092 --> 00:39:11,969
It must have been tough for you since I
was gone without a word, right?

568
00:39:14,388 --> 00:39:17,015
I covered for you and told the boss you
took a scheduled day off.

569
00:39:18,475 --> 00:39:20,226
- Manager Lee.
- There must be a reason

570
00:39:20,227 --> 00:39:21,895
why someone who's never done this before
would suddenly skip work.

571
00:39:23,564 --> 00:39:25,649
Thank you.
I'll be sure to repay you for this.

572
00:39:26,024 --> 00:39:27,025
But...

573
00:39:27,401 --> 00:39:29,027
why were you out yesterday?

574
00:39:29,528 --> 00:39:30,529
And your face...

575
00:39:32,823 --> 00:39:33,907
Well...

576
00:39:34,450 --> 00:39:36,159
Manager Lee, in your opinion

577
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:38,537
what do you think I did
when I was younger?

578
00:39:39,204 --> 00:39:40,205
What you did?

579
00:39:46,295 --> 00:39:47,962
Didn't you work at a car wash?

580
00:39:47,963 --> 00:39:49,756
You're so good at washing cars.

581
00:39:49,757 --> 00:39:51,633
No, not that.

582
00:39:54,344 --> 00:39:55,512
Just take a good look.

583
00:39:56,346 --> 00:39:57,473
Does anything come to mind?

584
00:39:58,015 --> 00:40:00,976
Like a certain
vibe I give off or something.

585
00:40:03,395 --> 00:40:04,396
- One.
- Oh my.

586
00:40:07,191 --> 00:40:08,192
- Two.
- What...

587
00:40:11,069 --> 00:40:12,112
One.

588
00:40:15,616 --> 00:40:16,867
- Manager Bong.
- Two.

589
00:40:19,244 --> 00:40:20,787
- What are you doing?
- I wasn't doing anything.

590
00:40:20,788 --> 00:40:21,830
Are you crazy?

591
00:40:22,206 --> 00:40:23,290
I'm not crazy, but...

592
00:40:26,543 --> 00:40:27,628
Go wash the car.

593
00:40:28,212 --> 00:40:29,713
Since you didn't do it yesterday.
Make it spotless.

594
00:40:30,047 --> 00:40:31,048
Yes, sir.

595
00:40:46,396 --> 00:40:48,816
How dare you? Taking a day off
without my permission?

596
00:40:49,316 --> 00:40:51,652
Manager Bong. When you take a day off

597
00:40:51,819 --> 00:40:54,446
from now on,
you get my permission first. Got it?

598
00:41:13,257 --> 00:41:14,258
Smack!

599
00:41:19,763 --> 00:41:21,472
When the hero is in danger

600
00:41:21,473 --> 00:41:23,267
their past just suddenly
comes flashing back.

601
00:41:41,577 --> 00:41:42,786
Boss!

602
00:41:55,382 --> 00:41:57,467
Boss. I need to take a half day.

603
00:41:58,051 --> 00:41:59,428
You told me to ask first.

604
00:41:59,636 --> 00:42:00,888
So I'm telling you, I'm taking one.

605
00:42:04,057 --> 00:42:05,058
A half day.

606
00:42:07,227 --> 00:42:08,270
Fine, take it.

607
00:42:09,938 --> 00:42:10,939
A half day.

608
00:42:21,158 --> 00:42:22,451
Seriously? Is this it?

609
00:42:23,911 --> 00:42:25,412
We take bank transfers too.

610
00:42:27,372 --> 00:42:28,457
Answer carefully.

611
00:42:28,582 --> 00:42:29,791
Excuse me, fellas.

612
00:42:32,502 --> 00:42:33,836
Can I ask you guys something?

613
00:42:33,837 --> 00:42:35,631
What is it? I'm busy. Can't you see?

614
00:42:35,881 --> 00:42:37,090
You don't look that busy.

615
00:42:38,091 --> 00:42:39,759
Enough with the tough-guy act.

616
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:41,345
Just answer my question.

617
00:42:41,803 --> 00:42:44,056
Which one of you is Kim Jin-su?

618
00:42:48,185 --> 00:42:49,186
That's me.

619
00:42:54,483 --> 00:42:55,692
Kim Jin-su.

620
00:42:58,445 --> 00:43:00,822
This isn't the guy I saw
on the motorcycle.

621
00:43:02,658 --> 00:43:04,159
So you're Jin-su.

622
00:43:05,202 --> 00:43:06,578
- Jin-su.
- Yeah?

623
00:43:07,329 --> 00:43:08,580
You own a motorcycle, right?

624
00:43:08,789 --> 00:43:10,289
Did you happen to lend
that motorcycle to anyone?

625
00:43:10,290 --> 00:43:11,500
And why should I tell you?

626
00:43:11,625 --> 00:43:12,833
Could you please tell me?

627
00:43:12,834 --> 00:43:14,378
It's really important that I find out.

628
00:43:14,503 --> 00:43:16,463
If it's that important to you

629
00:43:16,755 --> 00:43:17,965
then you should offer something for it.

630
00:43:18,298 --> 00:43:19,299
You expect it for free?

631
00:43:21,843 --> 00:43:22,844
Hold him.

632
00:43:26,974 --> 00:43:29,016
All right, let's see what you've got.

633
00:43:29,017 --> 00:43:30,852
If I like what I see, I'll tell you.

634
00:43:31,186 --> 00:43:34,231
Jeez, what should I do?
I don't have any money

635
00:43:34,773 --> 00:43:36,274
but I can give you something else.

636
00:43:45,701 --> 00:43:47,077
- Jin-su.
- Hey.

637
00:43:50,163 --> 00:43:52,249
Hey, what are you doing? Get him! Hurry!

638
00:43:52,582 --> 00:43:53,583
You!

639
00:44:11,476 --> 00:44:13,311
When an adult asks you a question

640
00:44:13,603 --> 00:44:16,481
you answer. Where are your manners?

641
00:44:17,315 --> 00:44:20,985
- Trying to throw a punch at me?
- Sir! Sir!

642
00:44:20,986 --> 00:44:22,612
It hurts!

643
00:44:28,660 --> 00:44:29,911
- Jin-su.
- Yes.

644
00:44:30,620 --> 00:44:32,789
- I'm going to ask you one more time.
- Yes.

645
00:44:33,123 --> 00:44:34,582
You own a motorcycle, right?

646
00:44:34,583 --> 00:44:35,667
That shiny one.

647
00:44:35,876 --> 00:44:37,753
- You mean my Scooter?
- Yes, that's the one. Your Scooter.

648
00:44:39,421 --> 00:44:40,922
That punk Heo Nam-il took it.

649
00:44:41,256 --> 00:44:42,257
Why?

650
00:44:42,716 --> 00:44:43,884
- Heo Nam-il?
- Yes.

651
00:44:47,846 --> 00:44:49,890
Is this guy trying to
drive me into the ground?

652
00:44:55,896 --> 00:44:57,481
Orthostatic hypotension...

653
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:19,961
Are you all right?

654
00:45:21,838 --> 00:45:22,839
I'm sorry.

655
00:45:25,634 --> 00:45:27,052
When did you get here?

656
00:45:28,512 --> 00:45:29,721
Just now.

657
00:45:30,972 --> 00:45:32,641
- But are you not feeling well?
- No, it's just...

658
00:45:32,808 --> 00:45:33,891
Well...

659
00:45:33,892 --> 00:45:35,352
I just...

660
00:45:35,769 --> 00:45:37,270
haven't been sleeping well lately.

661
00:45:38,230 --> 00:45:39,231
I'm sorry.

662
00:45:48,323 --> 00:45:49,782
Do you have the lunch box there?

663
00:45:49,783 --> 00:45:51,075
Lunch box? Oh, yes.

664
00:45:51,076 --> 00:45:52,285
Just a moment.

665
00:46:01,878 --> 00:46:03,255
- It's fried chicken with sweet sauce.
- Yes.

666
00:46:13,765 --> 00:46:15,100
Oh, please...

667
00:46:15,892 --> 00:46:18,019
don't feel obligated.

668
00:46:18,353 --> 00:46:21,897
Luckily what you mentioned was available

669
00:46:21,898 --> 00:46:23,150
so I decided to order it.

670
00:46:24,109 --> 00:46:25,277
It's...

671
00:46:26,153 --> 00:46:28,071
It's what we do for our regulars.

672
00:46:32,576 --> 00:46:34,035
You said you weren't sleeping well, right?

673
00:46:36,037 --> 00:46:37,664
Can you hold out your hand for me?

674
00:46:43,044 --> 00:46:44,838
This is how you do it for handcuffs.

675
00:46:45,338 --> 00:46:46,590
My arm's a bit numb.

676
00:46:47,924 --> 00:46:48,925
No, like this.

677
00:46:49,176 --> 00:46:50,177
Like this.

678
00:46:55,557 --> 00:46:58,977
This is what I have
when I'm on my night rounds

679
00:46:59,811 --> 00:47:01,605
and it works pretty well.

680
00:47:03,231 --> 00:47:05,192
Have some. It'll help you wake up.

681
00:47:05,942 --> 00:47:06,943
Okay.

682
00:47:10,071 --> 00:47:11,072
Thank you.

683
00:47:11,740 --> 00:47:12,782
Thank you, too.

684
00:47:18,788 --> 00:47:19,789
Goodbye.

685
00:47:20,957 --> 00:47:22,000
Bye.

686
00:47:23,210 --> 00:47:24,211
Take care.

687
00:47:51,738 --> 00:47:52,948
She said thanks.

688
00:48:05,543 --> 00:48:06,544
What?

689
00:48:14,511 --> 00:48:17,513
You said you couldn't sleep
and felt like you were dying

690
00:48:17,514 --> 00:48:19,391
so I dropped everything and rushed over.

691
00:48:19,724 --> 00:48:22,102
- You look just fine.
- Can't you see these dark circles?

692
00:48:22,602 --> 00:48:23,895
Forget it. You should go home.

693
00:48:24,896 --> 00:48:26,397
You must be exhausted
for all sorts of reasons.

694
00:48:26,398 --> 00:48:28,440
Who's the one who ditched work

695
00:48:28,441 --> 00:48:29,567
and ran off in the first place?

696
00:48:30,777 --> 00:48:32,445
Did I go out and mess around like you did?

697
00:48:33,363 --> 00:48:35,239
Our business that you don't care about

698
00:48:35,240 --> 00:48:36,616
our real business!

699
00:48:37,617 --> 00:48:40,495
I was doing that while you were
goofing off with that woman!

700
00:48:40,787 --> 00:48:42,497
You little punk.

701
00:48:49,129 --> 00:48:50,130
Go ahead.

702
00:48:50,505 --> 00:48:51,506
Hit me.

703
00:48:52,549 --> 00:48:54,926
I'd love to take a good punch for a
change. Go on, hit me.

704
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:56,761
Hit me.

705
00:49:03,143 --> 00:49:05,312
Let's cool off and talk about this later.

706
00:49:08,815 --> 00:49:10,233
You can't even hit me anymore?

707
00:49:12,402 --> 00:49:13,528
You know...

708
00:49:14,321 --> 00:49:16,739
I don't care about Gang Beom-ryong,
the owner of the Kind Convenience Store.

709
00:49:16,740 --> 00:49:18,992
I miss my old reckless boss

710
00:49:20,160 --> 00:49:22,329
Gang Beom-ryong from the Hwasan Sect.

711
00:49:22,829 --> 00:49:23,913
It's not working. Damn it.

712
00:49:44,017 --> 00:49:46,977
Gong-bok and Beom-ryong.
Those bastards show up after ten years

713
00:49:46,978 --> 00:49:48,396
and screw up my business?

714
00:49:49,856 --> 00:49:51,149
I should've just
finished them off back then.

715
00:49:54,402 --> 00:49:55,403
But, Boss...

716
00:49:55,945 --> 00:49:57,781
The guy who did this to us...

717
00:49:57,989 --> 00:50:01,493
do you really think he's connected to
Beom-ryong and Gong-bok?

718
00:50:01,826 --> 00:50:04,245
How dare you still
call his name so nicely?

719
00:50:05,663 --> 00:50:06,915
Look.

720
00:50:07,582 --> 00:50:09,249
Do you think it's a coincidence
that Gong-bok was there

721
00:50:09,250 --> 00:50:10,960
while you were getting beaten up?

722
00:50:12,003 --> 00:50:14,171
That bastard Gang Beom-ryong got rid of
Chairman Hwang Hwa-san

723
00:50:14,172 --> 00:50:15,715
to take his place, and now he's after me.

724
00:50:15,882 --> 00:50:17,967
He must've hired
some martial arts master or something.

725
00:50:19,427 --> 00:50:22,055
He can't fight me one-on-one like before,
so he pulls this kind of crap.

726
00:50:26,559 --> 00:50:30,563
This scar aches whenever it rains. I think
it's time for revenge.

727
00:50:31,439 --> 00:50:33,525
Boss, we heard from Sergeant Kim.

728
00:50:33,775 --> 00:50:35,693
- They've located both of them.
- Okay.

729
00:50:36,194 --> 00:50:37,904
- Everyone, get ready.
- Yes, Boss.

730
00:50:43,618 --> 00:50:44,868
Let's go!

731
00:50:44,869 --> 00:50:46,162
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

732
00:50:50,667 --> 00:50:51,668
So...

733
00:50:53,503 --> 00:50:56,172
- you got hit and your memory came back?
- No, before I got hit.

734
00:50:56,673 --> 00:50:59,133
I felt the baseball coming at me
from behind, and suddenly

735
00:50:59,134 --> 00:51:01,594
this scene just flashed through my mind.

736
00:51:03,221 --> 00:51:04,472
When I was younger...

737
00:51:05,598 --> 00:51:07,434
I had a six-pack

738
00:51:08,435 --> 00:51:09,810
and I kicked a dagger

739
00:51:09,811 --> 00:51:11,688
flying at me from behind!

740
00:51:12,397 --> 00:51:14,649
- You kicked a dagger? Come on.
- I'm serious!

741
00:51:15,233 --> 00:51:16,985
Try to hit me. Come on.

742
00:51:19,737 --> 00:51:20,738
Okay.

743
00:51:21,739 --> 00:51:23,116
I'll feel it coming and dodge.

744
00:51:34,252 --> 00:51:35,836
- Boss...
- Are they here?

745
00:51:35,837 --> 00:51:37,963
- Yes, they're here.
- Get in there, quickly!

746
00:51:37,964 --> 00:51:38,965
What the...

747
00:51:41,593 --> 00:51:43,177
So you little rats

748
00:51:43,178 --> 00:51:44,596
were hiding here, huh?

749
00:51:45,388 --> 00:51:46,723
What's this? Are you bowing to me?

750
00:51:53,062 --> 00:51:54,438
Hey, what's going on?

751
00:51:54,439 --> 00:51:55,522
What's this?

752
00:51:55,523 --> 00:51:56,774
What's going on?

753
00:51:57,108 --> 00:51:58,567
Hold on, it's not that.

754
00:51:58,568 --> 00:51:59,569
Wait a minute.

755
00:52:00,570 --> 00:52:02,279
What's going on?

756
00:52:02,280 --> 00:52:04,491
Did they know we were
coming or something? Damn it.

757
00:52:08,453 --> 00:52:09,454
Hey, hold on.

758
00:52:11,206 --> 00:52:12,624
Hold on.

759
00:52:20,215 --> 00:52:22,217
Damn, you scared me! Hey, get him!

760
00:52:22,550 --> 00:52:23,676
Hey, get that bastard!

761
00:52:24,052 --> 00:52:25,303
Jeez, you scared me.

762
00:52:34,854 --> 00:52:36,314
Welcome to Jumbo Convenience Store.

763
00:52:54,165 --> 00:52:55,375
Long time no see, Gong-bok.

764
00:53:15,562 --> 00:53:17,438
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

765
00:53:34,956 --> 00:53:36,624
Your food delivery is here.

766
00:53:38,793 --> 00:53:40,003
I'm coming in.

767
00:54:14,787 --> 00:54:16,496
The place is a mess.

768
00:54:16,497 --> 00:54:19,083
Someone might've beaten me to it.

769
00:54:23,379 --> 00:54:25,340
Yeongseon Steel.

770
00:54:29,510 --> 00:54:31,345
YEONGSEON FOOD

771
00:54:31,346 --> 00:54:32,639
Yeongseon...

772
00:54:33,348 --> 00:54:34,349
Food.

773
00:54:45,068 --> 00:54:46,401
You know...

774
00:54:46,402 --> 00:54:48,780
I don't care about Gang Beom-ryong,
the owner of the Kind Convenience Store.

775
00:54:49,155 --> 00:54:51,574
I miss my old reckless boss

776
00:54:52,575 --> 00:54:55,036
Gang Beom-ryong from the Hwasan Sect.

777
00:55:00,833 --> 00:55:02,085
Damn it.

778
00:55:13,763 --> 00:55:15,056
MA GONG-BOK

779
00:55:21,354 --> 00:55:23,773
MA GONG-BOK

780
00:55:25,066 --> 00:55:26,358
Hey, Gong-bok?

781
00:55:26,359 --> 00:55:28,653
Well, Beom-ryong, it's been a while.

782
00:55:29,654 --> 00:55:32,156
- Who is this?
- You don't recognize my voice?

783
00:55:32,407 --> 00:55:33,741
Come on, that hurts.

784
00:55:34,033 --> 00:55:35,034
It's me. In-gu.

785
00:55:37,745 --> 00:55:40,039
- How could you...
- We old Hwasan Sect guys

786
00:55:40,373 --> 00:55:41,582
should get together and catch up.

787
00:55:42,375 --> 00:55:44,210
I'll text you the location.

788
00:55:44,585 --> 00:55:46,254
Don't be late.

789
00:55:46,587 --> 00:55:48,588
I'm dying to see you.

790
00:55:48,589 --> 00:55:51,300
Boss, Beom-ryong, please help me.

791
00:55:57,765 --> 00:56:00,685
DON'T MAKE ME ANY ANGRIER

792
00:56:45,354 --> 00:56:47,148
Now I'm sure of it.

793
00:56:47,815 --> 00:56:49,192
The man who was in this house...

794
00:56:56,616 --> 00:56:57,867
is the missing Bulgae.

795
00:56:59,160 --> 00:57:01,913
Come on. I'm not asking
for anything difficult.

796
00:57:02,538 --> 00:57:04,414
I just asked you to find someone

797
00:57:04,415 --> 00:57:06,416
who worked with Han Gyeong-wook.

798
00:57:06,417 --> 00:57:07,501
Is that really so difficult?

799
00:57:07,502 --> 00:57:08,961
Do you want to get someone fired?

800
00:57:09,170 --> 00:57:11,756
Han Gyeong-wook used to work here.

801
00:57:11,881 --> 00:57:14,133
Do you have any idea how many connections
he still has in this company?

802
00:57:14,258 --> 00:57:16,092
He quit to get into politics.

803
00:57:16,093 --> 00:57:17,677
I'm sure those connections are long gone.

804
00:57:17,678 --> 00:57:19,179
They're still as strong as ever.

805
00:57:19,180 --> 00:57:20,181
Look, I'm hanging up.

806
00:57:20,348 --> 00:57:21,890
Don't drag me into your mess.

807
00:57:21,891 --> 00:57:23,726
No, wait. Just one more question. That's
it.

808
00:57:24,018 --> 00:57:26,646
- Just one more question.
- Get up, you hear me?

809
00:57:27,021 --> 00:57:28,022
This son of a bitch.

810
00:57:28,189 --> 00:57:29,857
Who the hell is this guy?

811
00:57:34,237 --> 00:57:36,405
Jeez, just tell us already.

812
00:57:37,782 --> 00:57:38,991
Hey. Who do you work for?

813
00:57:39,867 --> 00:57:41,661
I'm just his uncle.

814
00:57:42,703 --> 00:57:44,330
So you're not going to talk, huh?

815
00:57:45,665 --> 00:57:47,123
Well, you leave me no choice.

816
00:57:47,124 --> 00:57:48,876
I'm going to ask you some questions.

817
00:57:49,919 --> 00:57:51,461
And if I don't like your answers

818
00:57:51,462 --> 00:57:53,046
or you piss me off...

819
00:57:53,047 --> 00:57:54,549
you'll get the bat.

820
00:57:55,216 --> 00:57:56,801
So think carefully before you answer.

821
00:57:59,178 --> 00:58:00,346
You son of a bitch.

822
00:58:01,681 --> 00:58:03,015
Let's start with you, Gong-bok.

823
00:58:04,851 --> 00:58:06,936
You bastard, why'd you suddenly show up?

824
00:58:07,103 --> 00:58:09,564
I was just minding my own business at the
convenience store.

825
00:58:10,022 --> 00:58:13,024
You're the one who showed up
out of nowhere, you bastard, Yoo In-gu.

826
00:58:13,025 --> 00:58:14,277
Has this bastard lost his mind?

827
00:58:15,987 --> 00:58:18,155
Gong-bok, let's think about this
logically.

828
00:58:18,573 --> 00:58:22,243
Right when I'm trying to start a new
business on Yeongseon Island...

829
00:58:22,952 --> 00:58:25,830
at my business, Heaven Capital, which
that bastard destroyed

830
00:58:26,247 --> 00:58:27,748
you showed up with him.

831
00:58:28,457 --> 00:58:31,001
And you're telling me you're just an
innocent convenience store clerk?

832
00:58:31,002 --> 00:58:32,253
Is this all just a coincidence?

833
00:58:33,004 --> 00:58:34,337
Does that make any sense to you?

834
00:58:34,338 --> 00:58:36,591
I don't know
anything about it, you bastard.

835
00:58:39,010 --> 00:58:40,428
That's not the answer I wanted.

836
00:58:41,012 --> 00:58:42,013
Hey, get him up.

837
00:58:44,390 --> 00:58:45,474
Hurry.

838
00:58:49,896 --> 00:58:51,187
Come on, get him up.

839
00:58:51,188 --> 00:58:52,440
This bastard.

840
00:58:53,691 --> 00:58:54,859
We've got a customer.

841
00:59:29,393 --> 00:59:30,477
TWO NATIONAL INTELLIGENCE SERVICE AGENTS
CAUGHT COLLUDING WITH NORTH KOREA...

842
00:59:30,478 --> 00:59:33,481
THE MURDER OF DIRECTOR KWON SOON-BOK
GANG LEADER HWANG HWA-SAN IMPLICATED

843
00:59:34,649 --> 00:59:35,942
Ten years ago...

844
00:59:36,359 --> 00:59:37,984
the National Intelligence Service agents

845
00:59:37,985 --> 00:59:40,571
and the spy on the passenger ferry?

846
00:59:41,447 --> 00:59:43,199
Yes, that's the one.

847
00:59:44,241 --> 00:59:45,701
Who was in charge of it?

848
00:59:47,161 --> 00:59:48,453
Deputy Chief Han Gyeong-wook.

849
00:59:48,454 --> 00:59:49,789
Han Gyeong-wook?

850
00:59:51,499 --> 00:59:53,125
Oh, Han Gyeong-wook...

851
00:59:53,376 --> 00:59:55,670
Around that same time...

852
00:59:56,003 --> 00:59:59,923
he also arrested the culprit in the
murder of Director Kwon Soon-bok.

853
00:59:59,924 --> 01:00:02,301
- So, could these two cases be connected?
- Hey.

854
01:00:02,593 --> 01:00:03,886
That's all I can say.

855
01:00:04,428 --> 01:00:06,681
This case is classified.
It's orders from the top.

856
01:00:08,099 --> 01:00:10,226
This isn't like the other cases
you've handled.

857
01:00:10,601 --> 01:00:11,894
It's on a completely different level.

858
01:00:12,520 --> 01:00:14,271
Drop it now before you get hurt.

859
01:00:21,195 --> 01:00:22,613
Yes, Chief Kim.

860
01:00:24,073 --> 01:00:26,826
- What?
- He just suddenly crossed into my lane...

861
01:00:27,326 --> 01:00:30,036
- hit me, and just drove off.
- What about the other vehicle?

862
01:00:30,037 --> 01:00:32,039
I ran the plates...

863
01:00:32,498 --> 01:00:33,624
but it's a ghost car.

864
01:00:34,458 --> 01:00:35,710
A ghost car?

865
01:00:38,963 --> 01:00:41,506
Uncle. This is a dangerous situation.

866
01:00:41,507 --> 01:00:42,924
Do it already!

867
01:00:42,925 --> 01:00:44,384
Agent 007.

868
01:00:44,385 --> 01:00:46,137
I don't know! Just be quiet a minute.

869
01:00:50,057 --> 01:00:51,100
Just a second.

870
01:00:51,851 --> 01:00:53,227
Don't you have to get hit for it to work?

871
01:00:53,811 --> 01:00:54,894
Are you crazy?

872
01:00:54,895 --> 01:00:56,022
You're telling me to take a punch?

873
01:00:56,981 --> 01:00:58,566
- I'm still hurting from before.
- Hey!

874
01:00:59,150 --> 01:01:00,442
You two are next

875
01:01:00,443 --> 01:01:01,777
so keep your mouths shut.

876
01:01:10,036 --> 01:01:12,538
Man, this guy's tough.
He just won't break.

877
01:01:13,330 --> 01:01:16,082
You're dead when Beom-ryong gets here,
you son of a bitch.

878
01:01:16,083 --> 01:01:17,960
Yeah? But I looked into it

879
01:01:18,627 --> 01:01:21,380
and this Gang Beom-ryong has been a
convenience store owner for ten years.

880
01:01:21,964 --> 01:01:23,549
A guy who's done nothing but scan barcodes
for a decade...

881
01:01:24,425 --> 01:01:25,801
you think he's still got his old moves?

882
01:01:53,037 --> 01:01:54,830
All right, let's move
on to the next in line.

883
01:01:55,456 --> 01:01:56,707
Hey, Mr. Martial Arts Master.

884
01:01:58,709 --> 01:02:01,127
Did those guys hire you
to beat my son to a pulp?

885
01:02:01,128 --> 01:02:02,670
Wait, sir.

886
01:02:02,671 --> 01:02:04,465
Hired? No, I'm just...

887
01:02:04,799 --> 01:02:06,674
an ordinary office worker.

888
01:02:06,675 --> 01:02:08,177
Just a regular salaryman.

889
01:02:08,636 --> 01:02:10,638
He's not a Martial Arts Master,
he's a comedian.

890
01:02:11,222 --> 01:02:12,388
You're sure he's the one who beat you?

891
01:02:12,389 --> 01:02:13,516
Yes, boss, I'm telling you.

892
01:02:13,849 --> 01:02:15,851
He took one hit and passed out, but then

893
01:02:16,227 --> 01:02:18,229
he slowly got up like a zombie

894
01:02:18,437 --> 01:02:20,898
rolled his eyes back,
and went totally berserk. I swear.

895
01:02:22,900 --> 01:02:24,026
Um, excuse me.

896
01:02:25,778 --> 01:02:26,904
Go on and hit him.

897
01:02:28,697 --> 01:02:30,782
- Go on, just hit him once!
- Are you insane?

898
01:02:30,783 --> 01:02:32,325
What is he, the Hulk?
He transforms when you hit him?

899
01:02:32,326 --> 01:02:34,036
No! Sir, it's not like that.

900
01:02:34,203 --> 01:02:35,454
Are you out of your mind?

901
01:02:35,746 --> 01:02:37,790
- It's okay, trust me.
- Look at these two, having fun.

902
01:02:38,374 --> 01:02:39,375
Hey, go ahead and hit him.

903
01:02:42,044 --> 01:02:43,378
Are you sure this is okay?

904
01:02:43,379 --> 01:02:45,214
- Should I do it?
- No. I'll do it.

905
01:02:51,262 --> 01:02:52,388
What the hell?

906
01:02:52,805 --> 01:02:54,305
Don't get smart with me! Dammit!

907
01:02:54,306 --> 01:02:57,100
Hey, you idiot! Is that the best you can
do? Hit him harder!

908
01:02:57,101 --> 01:02:58,102
That was plenty hard...

909
01:03:01,147 --> 01:03:02,148
Uncle!

910
01:03:09,655 --> 01:03:10,906
- Uncle!
- Look.

911
01:03:11,323 --> 01:03:12,324
There it is!

912
01:03:14,243 --> 01:03:17,413
It hurts so much.

913
01:03:19,415 --> 01:03:20,416
Uncle...

914
01:03:23,127 --> 01:03:24,128
Uncle!

915
01:03:26,839 --> 01:03:28,298
It hurts so much.

916
01:03:28,299 --> 01:03:31,135
I keep telling you, I'm
just a regular office worker.

917
01:03:32,178 --> 01:03:33,679
Hey! Stomp him!

918
01:03:34,096 --> 01:03:35,347
Hey, wait!

919
01:04:02,625 --> 01:04:03,875
Hey, Ma Gong-bok

920
01:04:03,876 --> 01:04:06,628
did your precious
convenience store boss run off?

921
01:04:06,629 --> 01:04:08,380
Why isn't he showing up, huh?

922
01:04:09,256 --> 01:04:11,508
He's supposed to be getting
revenge for this scar.

923
01:04:19,975 --> 01:04:21,101
I guess there's no choice.

924
01:04:22,269 --> 01:04:23,354
You'll have to be the next best thing.

925
01:04:24,063 --> 01:04:25,731
So I guess I'll have to
take it out on you.

926
01:04:43,707 --> 01:04:44,708
What the hell?

927
01:05:29,962 --> 01:05:31,171
Boss!

928
01:05:34,425 --> 01:05:36,468
- Gang Beom-ryong, that bastard.
- You bastard.

929
01:05:38,012 --> 01:05:39,637
I haven't slept in two days

930
01:05:39,638 --> 01:05:40,973
and I'm freaking exhausted.

931
01:05:42,266 --> 01:05:43,309
Ma Gong-bok.

932
01:05:45,394 --> 01:05:47,479
Let's wrap this up quick and get out of
here.

933
01:05:57,865 --> 01:06:00,326
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

934
01:06:11,920 --> 01:06:13,756
Seriously, what do you think you're doing?

935
01:06:14,089 --> 01:06:15,424
You think I enjoyed living like this?

936
01:06:15,549 --> 01:06:18,093
This is all your fault, Jeong Ho-myeong.

937
01:06:18,302 --> 01:06:20,470
Hard-working citizens like yourself...

938
01:06:20,471 --> 01:06:22,348
that's who cops like me
are supposed to protect.

939
01:06:24,266 --> 01:06:26,601
No matter how pure it is

940
01:06:26,602 --> 01:06:28,729
it only takes a few storms
to turn the water muddy...

941
01:06:29,104 --> 01:06:31,482
- It happens in an instant.
- I don't understand. Why?

942
01:06:31,690 --> 01:06:33,525
Something's definitely off.
This whole thing smells fishy.

943
01:06:34,109 --> 01:06:36,235
Be careful.
This is your first mission in ten years.

944
01:06:36,236 --> 01:06:38,029
Oh, come on!

945
01:06:38,030 --> 01:06:39,281
Have you forgotten who I am?

946
01:06:39,615 --> 01:06:41,157
Don't let his looks fool you.

947
01:06:41,158 --> 01:06:43,160
He's the top black ops agent
for the National Intelligence Service.
